	•	keeps hypotheses adaptable
	•	good for discovery

2. Execution / reality layer (precise constraints)
	•	determines what actually works
	•	requires clear definitions
	•	tied to interfaces, capabilities, limits

The risk is when:

exploration-language starts substituting for execution-accuracy

